#Text=Keep a Busy Life Organized
#Text=After being so busy day after day , your life could become one giant mess .
#Text=Hopefully this wikiHow will help you to keep a busy life organized .
#Text=You may have to adapt some of the steps to fit your lifestyle .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Wake up early to get things done .
#Text=When you get up , clean up your room .
#Text=If you work until late , you might consider taking your showers at night so you can sleep an extra 20 minutes or so .
#Text=If pets , children or work schedules do n't allow you to do this , just try not to use the snooze function and shower when you get the chance .
#Text=Make sure you wake up early enough to actually get ready .
#Text=You may feel run down but you sure do n't have to look like it .
#Text=It will also help if you have everything that you need for the day packed up and ready to go .
#Text=Assuming you go to school , use every second of your time wisely .
#Text=Study halls , lunch breaks , and free time should n't be wasted .
#Text=It 's easy to daydream but instead of sitting in a sleepy stare , you could be working on homework you already know is going to be due or even other assignments .
#Text=Make it your goal to get as much done as possible at school .
#Text=Use planners and schedulers to plan time to get projects , readings , and other assignments finished .
#Text=Try not to procrastinate .
#Text=It 's something everyone is guilty of , but by doing a little work day by day it will ultimately be easier .
#Text=Eat healthy .
#Text=This might not seem important , but really it is .
#Text=You 'll have more energy and feel better .
#Text=Try to avoid take out foods , especially if you work in a restaurant !
#Text=Everyone realizes by now that coffee , snack cakes and McDonald 's meals really do add up and hit your wallet .
#Text=Pump yourself up for work .
#Text=Many people hate their jobs .
#Text=There will always be someone who you do n't like .
#Text=A task that you hate to do .
#Text=So on your way to work , try listening to your favorite songs .
#Text=Listen to songs that make you feel good or remind you of good times .
#Text=Make sure you get to work on time and are ready for the job .
#Text=Getting yelled at when you walk in the door first thing is never a good way to start a day 's work or shift .
#Text=Remember that 's it 's only a few hours of your day and you are making money .
#Text=And as hard as it , try to be pleasant to your coworkers .
#Text=Starting drama will not help anyone or solve any problems .
#Text=Be thankful when you get your paycheck that you have a job .
#Text=Some money is better than no money .
#Text=Make sure your bills are paid .
#Text=If you 're young , you probably have few bills to pay .
#Text=It helps to make a list of things you want and need .
#Text=Put the things you really need at the top .
#Text=Maybe your jeans are getting a little too thin to be considered nice , or your shoes are a bit worn out .
#Text=Think of things you really need .
#Text=Those should be the things you purchase first .
#Text=Then later come the wants .
#Text=Before you go splurge on one item , also think of future wants .
#Text=Will you want to get your hair done in a few weeks ?
#Text=Will you want to go to that concert later this summer ?
#Text=Do you want to redo your room ?
#Text=All of this things are wants and ultimately cost money as well ; think long term .
#Text=Do n't waste time when you get home .
#Text=It could be very easy to plop down in front of the computer and waste 2 hours on Facebook or staring at the TV screen for the night .
#Text=Try to avoid this because before you know it , it 'll be 1 AM and you still have n't moved since you got home .
#Text=Make sure you make time to spend with your loved ones and find ways to relieve your [ [ Reduce Stress|stress } } .
#Text=Do n't spend all your free time sleeping .
#Text=That may actually make you feel even more run down in the long run .
#Text=Go to bed at a reasonable time .
#Text=Try to get 8 hours of sleep ; it 's easier said then done for most of us .
#Text=Make life easier on yourself by doing the little things .
#Text=Make sure you have gas in your car .
#Text=Do n't put off stopping just because you 're tired .
#Text=If you ran out of gas in the middle of the road one day , you know you 'd not be happy .
#Text=Make sure you get your laundry done .
#Text=There 's nothing worse then doing a smell check to see what 's clean and what 's not .
#Text=Make sure you do n't carry around more than you need .
#Text=And do everyone a favor by not constantly complaining about your life .
#Text=Everyone goes through hard times and no one can really do anything to fix your problems .
#Text=Remember that work is just work .
#Text=It 's something you have to do and will most likely have to do for a very long time .
#Text=Do your job and do it well , and then leave the stress there as you walk out the door .
#Text=Do n't let school , work , and other stresses take over your life .
#Text=Remember it 's just apart of your day .
#Text=You are in actually a person !
#Text=Video
